servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and very thinly slice @red onion{1%unit}. Quarter @lime{1%unit}.

== Creamy Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, cilantro, and a few slices of onion to taste (you'll use the rest in the next step).

Toss with @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}, and juice from half the lime; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Pulled Chicken Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @BBQ pulled chicken{10%ounce} and cook, stirring, until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in juice from remaining lime. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

While filling cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{}. Fill with chicken filling and creamy slaw and serve.